tweet: Any surgical procedure post-delivery puts you at a higher risk of developing clots. Clots are easy to treat once discovered early-  Joseph Mutyaba #MwasuzeMutya  https://t.co/v2JBmEoxtL

name: SPARK TV
tweet: Developing high blood pressure while pregnant is also a risk factor for getting blood clots. Your doctor can prescribe blood thinner if he suspects that you might get blood clots-  Dr Joseph Mutyaba #MwasuzeMutya  https://t.co/UarwysBfT0

name: SPARK TV
tweet: People that have undergone orthopaedic surgery, spinal surgery and heart surgery or any surgery that required anaesthesia are at high risk of developing blood clots later. This is why physiotherapy is needed post-surgery- Dr Joseph Mutyaba #MwasuzeMutya  https://t.co/lnMGHFYE7U

name: SPARK TV
tweet: Another factor that has been linked to blood clots is cancer. It is possible to have cancer and be unaware of its existence in your body. Make it a habit to screen for common cancers like ovarian,prostate and breast cancer - Dr Joseph Mutyaba #MwasuzeMutya  https://t.co/Rkhgo2kxB4

name: SPARK TV
tweet: Staying hydrated keeps your blood from getting thick and forming dangerous clots. One way to check if you are drinking enough water is to look at the colour of your urine. If you are drinking enough after, the urine should be pale yellow- Dr Joseph Mutyaba #Mwasuzemutya  https://t.co/poJqKb4rm6

name: SPARK TV
tweet: Sitting for long periods of over 3 hours is dangerous because it restricts proper circulation of blood. It is advised to raise your legs when sitting - Dr Joseph Mutyaba #Mwasuzemutya  https://t.co/EftZ03QGpb

name: SPARK TV
tweet: Eating a high-fat meal causes the fat to build up in your arteries which slows down the blood flow to the heart. If the arteries get blocked, it can cause a  heart attack or stroke -  Dr Joseph Mutyaba #MwasuzeMutya  https://t.co/h1rRX2H1PA

name: SPARK TV
tweet: Edible fats like Margarine or Blue band are supposed to be eaten in moderation. To avoid blood clots, you need to reduce fatty foods in your diet and reheating or reusing cooking oil because it harms the arteries -  Dr Joseph Mutyaba #MwasuzeMutya  https://t.co/PuzwPpFz9y

name: SPARK TV
tweet: Any surgical procedure post-delivery puts you at a higher risk of developing clots. Clots are easy to treat once discovered early-  Joseph Mutyaba #MwasuzeMutya  https://t.co/v2JBmEoxtL

name: SPARK TV
tweet: Developing high blood pressure while pregnant is also a risk factor for getting blood clots. Your doctor can prescribe blood thinner if he suspects that you might get blood clots-  Dr Joseph Mutyaba #MwasuzeMutya  https://t.co/UarwysBfT0

name: SPARK TV
tweet: People that have undergone orthopaedic surgery, spinal surgery and heart surgery or any surgery that required anaesthesia are at high risk of developing blood clots later. This is why physiotherapy is needed post-surgery- Dr Joseph Mutyaba #MwasuzeMutya  https://t.co/lnMGHFYE7U

name: SPARK TV
tweet: Another factor that has been linked to blood clots is cancer. It is possible to have cancer and be unaware of its existence in your body. Make it a habit to screen for common cancers like ovarian,prostate and breast cancer - Dr Joseph Mutyaba #MwasuzeMutya  https://t.co/Rkhgo2kxB4

name: SPARK TV
tweet: Staying hydrated keeps your blood from getting thick and forming dangerous clots. One way to check if you are drinking enough water is to look at the colour of your urine. If you are drinking enough after, the urine should be pale yellow- Dr Joseph Mutyaba #Mwasuzemutya  https://t.co/poJqKb4rm6

name: SPARK TV
tweet: Sitting for long periods of over 3 hours is dangerous because it restricts proper circulation of blood. When you sit for very long and start feeling numb, it's because the blood remains in the legs. It is advised to raise your legs when sitting - Dr Joseph Mutyaba #Mwasuzemutya  https://t.co/EftZ03QGpb

name: SPARK TV
tweet: Eating a high-fat meal causes the fat to build up in your arteries which slows down the blood flow to the heart. If the arteries get blocked, it can cause a  heart attack or stroke -  Dr Joseph Mutyaba #MwasuzeMutya  https://t.co/h1rRX2H1PA

name: SPARK TV
tweet: Edible fats like Margarine or Blue band are supposed to be eaten in moderation. To avoid blood clots, you need to reduce fatty foods in your diet and reheating or reusing cooking oil because it harms the arteries -  Dr Joseph Mutyaba #MwasuzeMutya  https://t.co/PuzwPpFz9y
